      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">12.503</ph> Applicability of certain
laws to Executive agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial
items.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d711e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d732e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                   The following laws are not applicable
to Executive agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial
items:</p>
               <ol id="d711e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e16" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.chapter 65</xref>,
Contracts for Materials, Supplies, Articles, and Equipment Exceeding <ph rev="FAC 2020-06 June 5, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-007?>$10,000<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 12.503 by removing from paragraph (a)(1) “$15,000” and adding “$10,000” in its place.?></ph> (see <xref href="FAR-i1097464.dita#i1097464"
                              base="i1097464"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  22.6Contracts for Materials,
Supplies, Articles, and Equipment</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e31" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.3901(b)</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2306(b)</xref>,
Contingent Fees (see <xref href="FAR-i1124454.dita#i1124454"
                              base="i1124454"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">3.404</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e44" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.1708(e)(3)</xref>,
Minimum Response Time for Offers (see <xref href="FAR-i1120755.dita#i1120755"
                              base="i1120755"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">5.203</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e54" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.chapter 81</xref>,
Drug-Free Workplace (see <xref href="FAR-i1094542.dita#i1094542"
                              base="i1094542"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">23.501</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e64" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">31 U.S.C.1354(a)</xref>,
Limitation on use of appropriated funds for contracts with entities
not meeting veterans’ employment reporting requirements (see <xref href="FAR-i1096055.dita#i1096055"
                              base="i1096055"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">22.1302</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e74" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph>
                        
                         [Reserved]</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e79" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(7)</ph>
                        
                         Section
806(a)(3) of Pub. L. 102-190, as amended by Sections 2091 and 8105
of Pub. L. 103-355, (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2302</xref> note),
Payment Protections for Subcontractors and Suppliers (see <xref href="FAR-i1088884.dita#i1088884"
                              base="i1088884"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">28.106-6</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e90" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(8)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 4706(d)(1)</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2313(c)(1)</xref>,
GAO Access to Contractor Employees, Section 871 of Pub. L. 110-417
(see <xref href="FAR-i1060206.dita#i1060206"
                              base="i1060206"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.214-26</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1059150.dita#i1059150"
                              base="i1059150"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.215-2</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e106" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(9)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41U.S. C.2303,</xref> Policy
on Personal Conflicts of Interest by Contractor Employees (see subpart <xref href="FAR-i1123546.dita#i1123546"
                              base="i1123546"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">3.11</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d732e116" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                   Certain
requirements of the following laws are not applicable to executive
agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial items:</p>
               <ol id="d711e174" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e122" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title22-section2593a&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">22 U.S.C. 2593e</xref>, Requirement
for a certification under Measures Against Persons Involved in Activities
that Violate Arms Control Treaties or Agreements with the United
States (see <xref href="FAR-9.109.dita#id188RD6040HW"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">9.109</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e132" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">40 U.S.C.chapter 37</xref>,
Requirement for a certificate and clause under the Contract Work
Hours and Safety Standards statute (see <xref href="FAR-i1098333.dita#i1098333"
                              base="i1098333"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">22.305</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e142" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.8703</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8703</xref>, Requirement
for a clause and certain other requirements related to kickbacks
(see <xref href="FAR-i1124348.dita#i1124348"
                              base="i1124348"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">3.502</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e155" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">49 U.S.C.40118</xref>, Requirement
for a clause under the Fly American provisions (see <xref href="FAR-i1070062.dita#i1070062"
                              base="i1070062"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">47.405</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d732e165" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                   The applicability
of the following laws have been modified in regards to Executive
agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial items:</p>
               <ol id="d711e234" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e171" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.4704</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2402</xref>, Prohibition
on Limiting Subcontractor Direct Sales to the United States (see <xref href="FAR-i1124393.dita#i1124393"
                              base="i1124393"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">3.503</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e184" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.chapter 35,</xref> Truthful
Cost or Pricing Data, and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2306a</xref>, Truth
in Negotiations Act (see <xref href="FAR-i1105934.dita#i1105934"
                              base="i1105934"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15.403</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e197" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
